abstract_ssm: Ventana was founded by cultural workers who had toured Nicaragua in June and July 1983. Its activities included cultural exchanges with the Sandinista Cultural Workers Association (ASTC), collection of cultural supplies for Nicaraguan arts organizations, and support of anti-war networks and coalitions. The collection contains flyers, brochures, clippings, newspapers, and posters.
